<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,1657,1936]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,443,1657,1683]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[443,707,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">
— 
<taxonomicName box="[472,707,1657,1683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">Bertolonia cuspidata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity box="[899,1008,1657,1686]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.595" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" unit="km" value="3595.0">3,595 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity box="[1178,1268,1657,1686]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.95" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" unit="km" value="595.0">595 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Endangered” (EN), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[663,818,1693,1719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
