<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,1657,1936]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1765,1791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,532,1765,1791]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis box="[294,532,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Bertolonia cuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[706,774,1765,1791]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1261,1765,1791]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
), on shaded and moist slopes. Collected with flowers from July to February and fruits from August to March. The species can be recognized by the widely elliptic and glandulose-punctate leaf blades with a cuspidate apex, hypanthium glandulosepunctate and also glandulose-villose and petals with an apiculate apex ending in a glandular head. For more details see notes under 
<taxonomicName authority=", Bacci et al. (2018)" authorityName="Bacci" authorityYear="2018" box="[273,638,1909,1936]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis box="[273,413,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">B. cuspidata</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[427,638,1909,1936]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis box="[498,547,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<tableCitation box="[696,780,1909,1935]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
